  "text": "Here E is a fixed, real, energy-dimensioned parameter from the interval −mc 2 < E < mc 2 and µ (0) n ′ r κ (E) is a Sturmian eigenvalue; moreover, as we have previously assumed in Sec. 2, it holds that Z < α −1 /2. The reader should observe that this is the inverse of the Sturmian eigenvalue µ (0) n ′ r κ (E) which multiplies the Coulomb potential in the lower diagonal term of the differential operator in Eq. (4.10a). Proceeding as in Ref. [CITATION_1] , with some labor one finds that eigensolutions to the system (4.10) are µ",
