  "bib_entries": {
    "10409244": {
      "title": "The Dirac-Coulomb Sturmians and the series expansion of the DiracCoulomb Green function: application to the relativistic polarizability of the hydrogenlike atom",
      "abstract": "Closure relations satisfied by the radial Dirac-Coulomb Sturmians are proved analytically. The Sturmian expansion of the Dirac-Coulomb Green function is transformed to the form containing only series with summations running over non-negative indices. The main paper was published in J. Phys. B: At. Mol. Opt. Phys. 30 (1997) 825-61 [Erratum: 30 (1997) 2747], see also J. Phys. A: Math. Gen. 31 (1998) 4963--90 [Erratum: 31 (1998) 7415-6]."
